      "number": 1,
      "id": "I_kwDOTI8nP88AAAABHm5lhw",
      "title": "Does this have to be limited to JWTs?",
      "url": "https://github.com/skyfire-xyz/draft-skyfire-oauth-id-verification/issues/1",
      "state": "CLOSED",
      "author": "skyfire-ankit",
      "authorAssociation": "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "https://github.com/skyfire-xyz/draft-skyfire-oauth-id-verification/blob/efc37eb9653a320e9197c19109c96a600132d71c/draft-skyfire-oauth-id-verification.md?plain=1#L86\n\nHi @selfissued Does the universe of usage have to be JWTs?",
      "createdAt": "2026-07-03T18:11:49Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-07-03T21:26:35Z",
      "closedAt": "2026-07-03T21:21:04Z",
      "comments": [
        {
          "author": "selfissued",
          "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
          "body": "In theory, once the values are in the registry, they could also be used in other contexts.  Another specification could define such usage.  For instance, a spec could define their use in CWTs https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc8392.  But the purpose of this spec is defining the JWT claim and the values to use within it.",
          "createdAt": "2026-07-03T21:21:04Z",
          "updatedAt": "2026-07-03T21:21:04Z"
        },
        {
          "author": "skyfire-ankit",
          "authorAssociation": "CONTRIBUTOR",
          "body": "Makes sense \ud83d\udc4d ",
          "createdAt": "2026-07-03T21:26:35Z",
          "updatedAt": "2026-07-03T21:26:35Z"
        }
      ]
    },
